RACE.RACE_TEXT: GULFSTREAM PARK RACE 1 1 1/16M All Weather Track CR: 71. Maiden Claiming Purse 19000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MUFRIH stalked the pace in the four path, steadily gained on the pacesetter in the lane and inched ahead under a drive. LITTLE STEVEN set the pace in the three path, fought on inside of the winner, drifted out nearing the sixteenth pole and was narrowly outfinished. BANDERO raced off the pace four wide, rallied outside in the lane, drifted in a bit as LITTLE STEVEN drifted out nearing the sixteenth pole, steadied off that foe's heels and finished evenly from there. NOBLE TIGER was up close inside around the first turn, rated back early on the backstretch, continued to save ground off the pace around the far turn, rallied at the rail in upper stretch but failed to sustain the bid. HONOR GOLD raced in range two and three wide, bid between foes nearing the eighth pole and flattened out in the final furlong. NOBLE AND KIND raced in range four wide and lacked the needed rally. MUCHOMACHOMAC saved ground to no avail. BULLETONTHECHARTS failed to menace while racing three and four wide. TUMIGA broke a step slowly, raced well back two wide, went five wide around the far turn and never threatened. REDISUR steadied soon after the start, raced three and four wide and never contended. RULE IT played no factor while racing two wide. DOC BALLARD bobbled at the start and was outrun inside. AN OBJECTION LODGED BY THE RIDER OF BANDERO AGAINST LITTLE STEVEN FOR ALLEGED INTERFERENCE IN THE STRETCH WAS NOT ALLOWED.
